Matsudaira Izu-no-kami, masquerading as the lord of Satsuma, has learned there is only one sword school in all of Japan that can possibly defeat TMgM Shigekata’s Jigen-ryk. Matsudaira calls out the legendary Satsuma Osenshi cavalry to test these mysterious Taisha-ryk warriors—with their lives!

Over one million copies sold of the Dark Horse Lone Wolf and Cub editions.

description:
The sounds of this love penetrates deep into my heart…!

The budding DJ Sato has been idolizing Miri, the charismatic DJ for a long time before becoming a DJ himself. Miri starts to notice Sato and his raging jealousy drives his desire to monopolize Sato all to himself. Miri forces Sato to have sex with him after their fateful encounter one night but Sato doesn’t seem to dislike it?! The series about a frustrating love triangle, "Which One Is Your Boyfriend?" is also included. Featuring a bonus episode with lots of steamy, sweet, and sexy love scenes!

description: Since her "friends" framed her for the death of the class rabbit in elementary school, Mei Tachibana has given up on other people. But when Mei kicks Yamato, the most popular boy at her high school, in the head (she was aiming for someone else), she becomes enemy No. 1 among the student body... while Yamato himself grows more and more fascinated with her! How long can Mei keep her heart closed off? How long will she refuse to say, "I love you"? Candid and complex, Say I Love You breathes new life into common themes, thanks to Hazuki's unique insight into the awkward bluster and emotional vulnerability of teenage life.

Russ Heath is one to the finest artists in comic book history. In a career that began more than 70 years ago, he has worked for nearly every publisher. It is reproduced here meticulously scanned from the original art, and collected in a hardcover portfolio case.
